Release Notes:  HRRR v3.0.2


v3.0.2 - released September 25, 2018
* Changes to HRRR for FV3GFS implementation
   * Modified the EnKF processing code to be able to process the FV3GDAS EnKF files


* Repository Details
   * After cloning the hrrr.v3.0.2 branch of the EMC_hrrr git repository using the command below, retrieve the new code from the hrrr.v3 directory.
      * git clone -b hrrr.v3.0.2 https://${USER}@vlab.ncep.noaa.gov/code-review/a/EMC_hrrr hrrr.v3.0.2
      * git clone -b hrrr.v3.0.2 ssh://${USER}@vlab.ncep.noaa.gov:29418/EMC_hrrr hrrr.v3.0.2
   * The build script is located here: hrrr.v3.0.2/hrrr.v3/sorc/build_hrrr_all.sh
   * To build the code, run build_hrrr_all.sh and specify which codes you would like compiled within the script ("yes" or "no" switches).


* parm, scripts, and sorc files changed
   * parm/alaska/hrrrak_process_enkf.anl
   * parm/conus/hrrr_process_enkf.anl
   * scripts/alaska/exhrrr_prep_enkf.sh.ecf
   * scripts/conus/exhrrr_prep_enkf.sh.ecf
   * sorc/hrrr_process_enkf.fd/get_gefs_for_regional.enspro.f90
   * sorc/hrrr_process_enkf.fd/gfsp2wrfg.f90


* revised executables
   * hrrr_process_enkf

    
* implementation instructions
   * Retrieve the new parm, scripts, and sorc files 
   * Recompile the process_enkf code
   * Edit exhrrr_prep_enkf.sh.ecf for CONUS and Alaska - refer to lines 57-65 for path-relative variables
   * Need to test FV3GFS upgrade concurrently

